Ever.

1547
01:15:58,286 --> 01:15:59,548
I know.

1548
01:15:59,588 --> 01:16:02,853
I just...

1549
01:16:04,793 --> 01:16:07,455
Oh, Mom, I couldn't
handle it anymore.

1550
01:16:07,495 --> 01:16:08,928
- I just couldn't handle it.
- What?

1551
01:16:08,964 --> 01:16:11,489
What couldn't you handle?
You're young, you're smart,

1552
01:16:11,532 --> 01:16:15,195
you're energetic. You got this
incredibly bright future ahead of you.

1553
01:16:15,236 --> 01:16:16,669
It was too bright, Ma.
All right?

1554
01:16:16,704 --> 01:16:19,104
I just-- I just, I got--
I had to get away.

1555
01:16:19,140 --> 01:16:21,108
And do this?

1556
01:16:21,142 --> 01:16:23,542
You understand?
Every night shift I worked,

1557
01:16:23,578 --> 01:16:26,138
every overtime hour
I accepted,

1558
01:16:26,180 --> 01:16:29,172
I did it because I wanted
something better for you than I had.

1559
01:16:30,184 --> 01:16:32,948
Nanny!
Good, you're up.

1560
01:16:32,988 --> 01:16:34,478
Just leave that there.

1561
01:16:34,523 --> 01:16:37,788
So listen, the spa
was just awful,

1562
01:16:37,825 --> 01:16:41,261
totally overrun
with suburban riffraff.

1563
01:16:41,295 --> 01:16:43,286
And then in the middle
of my body scrub,

1564
01:16:43,331 --> 01:16:45,925
Mr. X called
and believe it or not,

1565
01:16:45,968 --> 01:16:48,732
he wants to take us
all to Nantucket next week.

1566
01:16:48,769 --> 01:16:51,829
So I figured I might as well
cut my trip short and...

1567
01:16:53,909 --> 01:16:56,104
Who's this?

1568
01:16:56,143 --> 01:16:57,838
I'm Judy.

1569
01:16:57,879 --> 01:17:00,370
It's my mom.

1570
01:17:01,515 --> 01:17:04,507
You never mentioned
you had a mother, Nanny.

1571
01:17:04,552 --> 01:17:07,316
Um...

1572
01:17:07,355 --> 01:17:10,017
my mom's a nurse.
She came over here to help me.

1573
01:17:10,057 --> 01:17:13,220
Grayer's been very
very very sick.

1574
01:17:13,260 --> 01:17:15,558
- I tried calling you--
- Where is he?

1575
01:17:15,597 --> 01:17:19,033
Well he's--
he's sleeping now.

1576
01:17:19,066 --> 01:17:21,125
Then he can't be
that sick now, can he?

1577
01:17:21,168 --> 01:17:23,500
So listen, could you
quickly unpack my luggage

1578
01:17:23,537 --> 01:17:25,505
and just put everything
in the laundry?

1579
01:17:25,539 --> 01:17:28,531
I'm exhausted and Mr. X is expected
sometime before 9:00.

1580
01:17:28,576 --> 01:17:30,976
I will see you
in the morning.

1581
01:17:31,012 --> 01:17:34,209
Oh, very nice
to meet you, Julie.

1582
01:17:34,248 --> 01:17:35,977
Judy.

1583
01:17:41,722 --> 01:17:43,383
[door closes]

1584
01:17:47,829 --> 01:17:51,697
Call me when this phase
of your life is over.

1585
01:17:55,369 --> 01:17:58,896
Annie's voice: I desperately wanted
to yell out after her,

1586
01:17:58,940 --> 01:18:00,908
but it was like one of
those awful dreams

1587
01:18:00,942 --> 01:18:03,035
where I had no voice.

1588
01:18:03,077 --> 01:18:06,046
- My desire to be an observer of life...
- [door closes]

1589
01:18:06,080 --> 01:18:08,947
